Many Christian schools give priority to families who regularly attend services . 
  But a group of vicars say it can lead to discrimination against the poor . 
  They say the system is open to abuse and many oversubscribed schools reject non-churchgoing families . 
  Left-leaning clergy and laypeople called for an end to religious selection . 
  Claimed the Church was being ‘turned to the advantage of those who are already advantaged’ The Church of England labelled their arguments ‘doctrinaire’